MARGARET C. SPELLMAN v. HOWARD C. SPELLMAN. [Nos. 17, 18,

October Term, 1935.]

Decided November 22nd, 1935.

The cause was argued before Bond, , C. J., Urner, Óffutt, Parke, Sloan, Mitchell, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ.

William T. Tippett, with whom was James E. Tippett on the brief, for the appellant. Lester L. Barrett, with whom was Joshua S. Hull on the brief, for the appellee. Shehan, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
